<p>I'm trying to get a PDO query running, so I'm doing:</p>  <pre><code>$src = $this-&gt;conn-&gt;prepare("SELECT name, model, software FROM product WHERE                               model LIKE '%:search_string%' OR                               name LIKE '%:search_string%' OR                               software LIKE '%:search_string%'"); $src-&gt;bindParam(':search_string', $search_string); $src-&gt;execute(); return $src-&gt;fetchAll(); </code></pre>  <p>But when I <code>var_dump</code> this, I always get an empty array ( <code>[]</code> ). However, if I change it to just "<code>SELECT name, model, software FROM product</code>", I get all of the products, just as expected, so how am I using the <code>LIKE</code> clause wrong? Or am I doing this completely wrong?</p>